Classify this text into a knowledge domain.

Text: "{{text}}"

Existing domains: {{existingDomains}}

Rules:
- If the text is SPECIFICALLY about an existing domain's core focus, return that exact domain name
- If the text is about a RELATED but DISTINCT field, create a new domain — do NOT collapse related fields into one domain. For example: "game-theory" and "auction-theory" are related but distinct; "network-routing" and "graph-theory" are related but distinct.
- If no existing domain fits, create a SHORT domain slug (1-3 words, kebab-case, e.g. "topic-area", "sub-topic-focus")
- Domain names should be category-level labels, NOT the full topic
- When in doubt, create a new domain rather than forcing content into a loosely related existing one

Respond with ONLY JSON: {"domain": "domain-name"}